== Battle ==
[[File:FFI PSP Blaze 4.png|Blaze in the ''20th Anniversary'' version.|thumb]]

Chaos's unique version of Blaze is a strong [[Fire (Final Fantasy element)|fire-elemental]] attack that is more powerful than any other monster ability of the same name. Tsunami and Cyclone deal heavy non-elemental damage and Earthquake is an [[Earth (Final Fantasy)|earth-elemental]] [[KO (Final Fantasy)|instant kill]]. Chaos attacks primarily with the three elements of fire, [[Ice (Final Fantasy element)|ice]] and [[Lightning (Final Fantasy)|lightning]], debilitating physical fighters with Slowra and increasing his physical capability with Haste, as well as healing himself to full health with Curaja. To finish off, he uses his most powerful attack, Flare.

=== Strategy ===
[[File:FFI Slowra EA.png|Slowra in the ''20th Anniversary'' version.|thumb|left]]
It is wise to give three characters a [[Ribbon (Final Fantasy)|Ribbon]]. In the NES, ''Origins'' and ''Pixel Remaster'' versions, there are only three Ribbons, so one party member will have to make it without. It is recommended to give the Ribbons to the mages. In the other versions, the player can get a fourth Ribbon, so one can give Ribbons to every party member. The Ribbons mitigate damage from most of Chaos's spells, as well as resisting the paralysis from his physical attacks and the instant death caused by Earthquake. Characters without a Ribbon should have [[NulAll (Final Fantasy)|NulAll]] cast on them by a [[White Mage (Final Fantasy)#White Wizard|White Wizard]], or at the very least, [[NulDeath (Final Fantasy)|NulDeath]] by a White or [[Red Mage (Final Fantasy)#Red Wizard|Red Wizard]] to avoid paralysis and instant death. [[Protect Ring (Final Fantasy)|Protect Rings]] cannot block Earthquake as it is earth-elemental and not death-elemental. Slowra can be countered with [[Haste (Final Fantasy)|Haste]] using either [[Thief (Final Fantasy)#Ninja|Ninjas]], [[Black Mage (Final Fantasy)#Black Wizard|Black Wizards]] or Red Wizards. In versions that have them, [[Hermes' Shoes (Final Fantasy)|Hermes' Shoes]] can also be used for Haste.

Chaos resists every element and has high magic defense, so weapon strikes work the best. [[Warrior (Final Fantasy)#Knight|Knights]], [[Thief (Final Fantasy)#Ninja|Ninjas]], [[Monk (Final Fantasy)#Master|Masters]] and, if unneeded for healing, Red Wizards, should all have Haste cast upon them. [[Temper (Final Fantasy)|Temper]] should be used on the physical fighters unless the version being played is the original NES/Famicom where the [[Magic bugs|spell is bugged]]. Physical fighters can use the [[Giant's Gloves (Final Fantasy)|Giant's Gloves]] to boost their attack power even faster than with Temper, though if the party has casters who know Temper, they can buff and attack in the same turn. Buffing should be done up until Chaos casts Curaja, which is the party's cue to go heavily offensive before Chaos reaches Curaja again in his spell cycle. For ''Dawn of Souls'' and later versions, [[Strength Tonic (Final Fantasy)|Strength Tonics]] and [[Speed Drink (Final Fantasy)|Speed Drinks]] are effective offensive buffs that can be used by characters without Black Magic to accelerate the damage boost.

To help defend against Chaos's physical attacks, the party should use [[Invisira]] (either cast by White or Red Wizards, or by [[Item magic|using]] the [[White Robe (Final Fantasy)|White Robe]] item) and [[Protera (Final Fantasy)|Protera]]. For ''Dawn of Souls'' and later, [[Giant's Tonic (Final Fantasy)|Giant's Tonics]] can also help to survive Chaos's attacks by maximizing the party to 999 HP. Afterwards, White Wizards should focus on healing with [[Healaga]] to [[Group-cast|target the entire party]]. Without a White Wizard, high [[Intelligence (stat)|Intelligence]] characters, like the Black Wizard and Red Wizard, should use the [[Healing Staff (Final Fantasy)|Healing Staff]] and/or [[Healing Helm (Final Fantasy)|Healing Helms]] when the entire party needs to be healed. The Red Wizard can fall back to [[Curaga (Final Fantasy)|Curaga]] if only a single target needs HP restored. If a Black Wizard finished buffing and has a free turn, he can attack with Flare.

If the party has few high Intelligence characters, it may be necessary to have three party members healing with the Healing Staff and Healing Helms and only one character focused on attacking.
{{clear}}

== Other appearances ==
=== ''[[Final Fantasy All the Bravest]]'' ===
[[File:Chaos ATB.png|right]]
{{Quote|This lord of discord thrives on strife. His knees subscribe to the same ideology, as well.|In-game description}}
Chaos is fought in Cornelia's Tract. He uses Beatdown and drops the Bastard Sword upon defeat.
